Wash and dry produce. Halve, peel, and finely dice @yellow onion{1}. Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}. Trim and quarter @zucchini{1} lengthwise; cut crosswise into ½-inch-thick pieces. Drain @cannellini beans{1%400g can}. Pick @thyme{¼%ounce} leaves from stems; mince leaves until you have 1 tsp. Roughly chop @parsley{¼%ounce}.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a large #pot over medium-high heat. Add onion; cook, stirring occasionally, until softened, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Add garlic; cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir zucchini, beans, minced thyme, @tomato paste{1.5%ounce}, @mushroom stock concentrate{2}, 3½ cups water, and a big pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{} into pot.

Bring to a boil, then reduce to a low simmer; cook, uncovered, until zucchini is just softened, ~{6-9%minutes}.

Stir @Israeli couscous{2.5%ounce} into pot. Cover and cook until couscous is tender, ~{7-9%minutes}. Taste and season generously with salt and pepper.

Divide soup between bowls. Top with @crème fraîche{2%tbsp}. Garnish with chopped parsley and serve.

> TIP: Cut a corner of the crème fraîche pouch to create a piping bag!